<TITLE> Land registration to be 'one-stop' from Sept1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 06 (bdnews24.com)  Submission of fees and taxes for land registration will become a 'one-stop service' from Sept 1, said finance minister AMA Muhith on Saturday. "This is being undertaken to ensure a smooth service and lessen the hassle of land registration," he said in a meeting with land officials and registrars organised by the law ministry at the BIAM auditorium. It would also lessen corruption and anomalies, he said. The government was moving to digitalise the entire land management system, said Muhith. Once complete, people will be able to collect land documents within 15 days, he said. "But time will be needed to amend the related laws and the current system," said the minister. b
